{"title_page": "1994 Polynesia Cup", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name =\n| year = 1994\n| othertitles =\n| image = \n| size = \n| caption = \n| country = Western Samoa\n| country2 = \n| dates = \n| num_teams = 4\n| confederations = 1\n| finalists = 4\n| venues = \n| cities = \n| champion =Tahiti\n| count = 1\n| second = Tonga\n| third =  Western Samoa\n| matches = 6\n| goals = 22\n| attendance = \n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| updated = \n}}\nThe '''[[Polynesia Cup]]''' 1994 was the first [[Polynesia]]-wide tournament ever held. It took place in [[Samoa|Western Samoa]] (later known as Samoa) and four teams participated: [[Tahiti]], [[Western Samoa]], [[American Samoa]] and [[Tonga]] and served for the first time as [[Oceania Nations Cup]] qualifier.\n\nThe teams played each other according to a round-robin format with [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] winning the tournament for the first time and qualifying to the [[1996 OFC Nations Cup]].\n\n==Results==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL|section=Table\n|update=complete\n|source=\n|team1=TAH|name_TAH={{fb|TAH}}\n|team2=TGA|name_TGA={{fb|TGA}}\n|team3=SAM|name_SAM={{fb|SAM|name=Western Samoa}}\n|team4=ASA|name_ASA={{fb|ASA}}\n|win_TAH=3|draw_TAH=0|loss_TAH=0|gf_TAH=10|ga_TAH=1|status_TAH=C\n|win_TGA=1|draw_TGA=1|loss_TGA=1|gf_TGA=4|ga_TGA=4\n|win_SAM=1|draw_SAM=1|loss_SAM=1|gf_SAM=5|ga_SAM=10|status_SAM=H\n|win_ASA=0|draw_ASA=0|loss_ASA=3|gf_ASA=3|ga_ASA=7\n|res_col_header=Q|result1=KO|col_KO=gold\n|text_KO=Champion\n}}</onlyinclude>\n{{Footballbox | date = 24 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|TAH}} \n|score = 1-0\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|TGA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 24 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|SAM|name=Western Samoa}} \n|score = 3-1\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|ASA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 25 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|TAH}} \n|score = 2-1\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|ASA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 25 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|SAM|name=Western Samoa}} \n|score = 2-2\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|TGA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 28 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|TGA}} \n|score = 2-1\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|ASA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 28 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|SAM|name=Western Samoa}} \n|score = 0-7\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|TAH}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n\n'''[[Tahiti]] qualified for [[Oceania Nations Cup 1996]]'''\n\n==References==\n*{{cite web |last1=Morrison |first1=Neil |title=Polynesian Cup 1994 |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/polynesia94.html |website=www.rsssf.com |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation |accessdate=22 April 2020}}\n\n{{Polynesia Cup}}\n\n[[Category:Polynesia Cup]]\n[[Category:1994\u201395 in OFC football|Wan]]\n[[Category:International association football competitions hosted by Samoa|1994]]\n[[Category:1996 OFC Nations Cup]]\n[[Category:1994 in Samoan sport]]\n\n\n{{Oceania-footy-competition-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name =\n| year = 1994\n| othertitles =\n| image = \n| size = \n| caption = \n| country = Western Samoa\n| country2 = \n| dates = \n| num_teams = 4\n| confederations = 1\n| finalists = 4\n| venues = \n| cities = \n| champion =Tahiti\n| count = 1\n| second = Tonga\n| third =  Western Samoa\n| matches = 6\n| goals = 22\n| attendance = \n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| updated = \n}}\nThe '''[[Polynesia Cup]]''' 1994 was the first [[Polynesia]]-wide tournament ever held. It took place in [[Samoa|Western Samoa]] (later known as Samoa) and four teams participated: [[Tahiti]], [[Western Samoa]], [[American Samoa]] and [[Tonga]] and server for the first time as [[Oceania Nations Cup]] qualifier.\n\nThe teams played each other according to a round-robin format with [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] winning the tournament for the first time and qualifying to the [[1996 OFC Nations Cup]].\n\n==Results==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL|section=Table\n|update=complete\n|source=\n|team1=TAH|name_TAH={{fb|TAH}}\n|team2=TGA|name_TGA={{fb|TGA}}\n|team3=SAM|name_SAM={{fb|SAM|name=Western Samoa}}\n|team4=ASA|name_ASA={{fb|ASA}}\n|win_TAH=3|draw_TAH=0|loss_TAH=0|gf_TAH=10|ga_TAH=1|status_TAH=C\n|win_TGA=1|draw_TGA=1|loss_TGA=1|gf_TGA=4|ga_TGA=4\n|win_SAM=1|draw_SAM=1|loss_SAM=1|gf_SAM=5|ga_SAM=10|status_SAM=H\n|win_ASA=0|draw_ASA=0|loss_ASA=3|gf_ASA=3|ga_ASA=7\n|res_col_header=Q|result1=KO|col_KO=gold\n|text_KO=Champion\n}}</onlyinclude>\n{{Footballbox | date = 24 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|TAH}} \n|score = 1-0\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|TGA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 24 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|SAM|name=Western Samoa}} \n|score = 3-1\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|ASA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 25 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|TAH}} \n|score = 2-1\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|ASA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox | date = 25 November 1994\n|team1 = {{Fb-rt|SAM|name=Western Samoa}} \n|score = 2-2\n|report= \n|team2 = {{Fb|TGA}} \n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Samoa|Western Samoa]]| attendance =  | referee = \n}}\n----\n{{Footballbox 